## SocketIO Rooms

- `class_{class_id}` — professor's faculty dashboard
- `enrolled_{class_id}` — student devices

## Event Rules

- Emit to BOTH rooms when state affects prof AND students (`settings_updated`, `class_started/stopped`)
- Student interactions → `class_{id}` only (prof dashboard)
- Poll start/stop → `class_{id}` (dashboard) + `enrolled_{id}` (student devices)
- Always verify student enrollment before emitting to student rooms
- Never block the SocketIO thread — keep handlers fast

## Event Catalog

**Server → Client:** `class_started/stopped`, `student_joined`, `student_interaction`, `poll_started/stopped/responses_cleared`, `poll_response`, `settings_updated`, `all_hands_cleared`, `thumbs_reactions_cleared`, `participation_grade_*`

**Client → Server:** `join_class`, `leave_class`, `join_student_enrollments`, `get_live_stats`

`get_live_stats` must return complete snapshot — `/api/live_dashboard` is REST equivalent for initial load.
